roduced in gaps nearer to the spinning neutron star. The\nuniversality of these results should become clearer as current computational\nrestrictions are overcome and boundary conditions are refined. Continued and\ncombined polarimetric, spectral, and temporal measurements should aid us in\nscrutinising these new emission models in our persistent pursuit of a deeper\nunderstanding of the pulsar marvel.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 2 Feb 2017 16:10:49 GMT"}],"update_date":"2017-02-03"}
