minated, and the accretion process\naccounts for 80 per cent of the radio luminosity when summed across the\nobjects. The radio emission connected with accretion appears to be correlated\nwith the optical luminosity of the RQQ, whilst a weaker luminosity-dependence\nis evident for the radio emission connected with star formation.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 3 Feb 2017 04:14:04 GMT"}],"update_date":"2017-02-06"}
